children.text: The steel lintel that supports the brickwork over this opening does not have sufficient end bearing.
The relevant Australian Standard, AS 3700 Masonry Structures, states in section 4.12 Arches and Lintels that
‘End bearings of lintels on each side of an opening shall be not less than 100mm in length for openings up to 1000mm wide and 150mm for wider openings’
, whereas Australian Standard AS 4773 Masonry for Small Buildings, requires in clause 8.2.2 Detailing of steel lintels that
‘A lintel shall extend beyond the opening at each end by at least the bearing lengths shown in Table 8.3’ .
The brickwork over this lintel will need to be demolished and reconstructed to ensure that the minimum end bearing is achieved to support the brickwork.
